  pages         = {1-42},
  issn          = {0218-1940},
  abstract      = {The use of formal methods early in the development process
                  has been advocated as a way of improving the quality of
                  software products and their production process. Here we
                  study the influence of a formal requirements document on
                  the next phase in the software process, that is design. We
                  suggest that formal design should coherently follow from
                  formal requirements. We show that two different formal
